<subSubSection id="78879BECFFBFFF846DB080A2FAC30860" pageId="2" pageNumber="197" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="3022C867FFBFFF846DB080A2FAC30860" blockId="2.[151,1437,1093,1876]" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">
<emphasis id="02E91475FFBFFF846DB080A2FED809BE" bold="true" box="[199,322,1201,1227]" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male imago can be separated from 
<taxonomicName id="F79DB3E4FFBFFF846FA480A1FCDB09B9" authorityName="Thomas &amp; Orth, 2000 in Thomas, Orth, Horeau &amp; Dominique" authorityYear="2000" box="[723,833,1202,1228]" class="Insecta" family="Leptophlebiidae" genus="Bessierus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="197" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="doloris">
<emphasis id="02E91475FFBFFF846FA480A1FCDB09B9" box="[723,833,1202,1228]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">B. doloris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following combination of characters: (1) penis lobes closer to each other, almost touching (
<figureCitation id="A8A6D4E2FFBFFF846FF780C5FCBD0985" box="[640,807,1238,1264]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[186,1404,185,1953]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[179,1408,181,1953]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male imago of Bessierus riobranco sp. n. a. forewing; b. body, dorsal view; c. body, lateral view; d. genitalia, ventral view; e. penes, ventral view; f. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4397236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4397236/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">Figs 3d and 3e</figureCitation>
); (2) base of each penis lobe, on outer margin, expanded (
<figureCitation id="A8A6D4E2FFBFFF846DD780E9FF6B0861" box="[160,241,1274,1300]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[186,1404,185,1953]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[179,1408,181,1953]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male imago of Bessierus riobranco sp. n. a. forewing; b. body, dorsal view; c. body, lateral view; d. genitalia, ventral view; e. penes, ventral view; f. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4397236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4397236/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">Fig. 3e</figureCitation>
); (3) telopenis slender (
<figureCitation id="A8A6D4E2FFBFFF846C8D80E9FDD60861" box="[506,588,1274,1300]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[186,1404,185,1953]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[179,1408,181,1953]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male imago of Bessierus riobranco sp. n. a. forewing; b. body, dorsal view; c. body, lateral view; d. genitalia, ventral view; e. penes, ventral view; f. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4397236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4397236/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">Fig. 3e</figureCitation>
); (4) inner margin of basal 1/3 of forceps segment I straight (
<figureCitation id="A8A6D4E2FFBFFF84698E80E9FAD60860" box="[1273,1356,1274,1301]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[186,1404,185,1953]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[179,1408,181,1953]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male imago of Bessierus riobranco sp. n. a. forewing; b. body, dorsal view; c. body, lateral view; d. genitalia, ventral view; e. penes, ventral view; f. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4397236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4397236/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">Fig. 3d</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="78879BECFFBFFF846DB0810EFDE00BD5" pageId="2" pageNumber="197" type="description">
<paragraph id="3022C867FFBFFF846DB0810EFC190B09" blockId="2.[151,1437,1093,1876]" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">
<emphasis id="02E91475FFBFFF846DB0810EFE6B0842" bold="true" box="[199,497,1309,1336]" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">Description. Male imago.</emphasis>
Length of body 
<quantity id="F7656582FFBFFF846FD0810DFD64084D" box="[679,766,1310,1336]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.3" pageId="2" pageNumber="197" unit="mm" value="4.3">4.3 mm</quantity>
, forewing length 4.0 mm, cerci broken and missing. General coloration: yellowish brown. 
<emphasis id="02E91475FFBFFF846C978151FDBA0829" bold="true" box="[480,544,1346,1372]" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="A8A6D4E2FFBFFF846F588151FD4D0829" box="[559,727,1346,1372]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[186,1404,185,1953]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[179,1408,181,1953]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male imago of Bessierus riobranco sp. n. a. forewing; b. body, dorsal view; c. body, lateral view; d. genitalia, ventral view; e. penes, ventral view; f. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4397236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4397236/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">Figs 3b and 3c</figureCitation>
): light brown, tinged with orange between ocelli; upper portion of eyes orangish, lower portion black; ocelli white, surrounded with black. Antennae light yellow brown. 
<emphasis id="02E91475FFBFFF8468338175FA0708F5" bold="true" box="[1348,1437,1382,1408]" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="A8A6D4E2FFBFFF846DE88199FEDD08D1" box="[159,327,1418,1444]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[186,1404,185,1953]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[179,1408,181,1953]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male imago of Bessierus riobranco sp. n. a. forewing; b. body, dorsal view; c. body, lateral view; d. genitalia, ventral view; e. penes, ventral view; f. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4397236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4397236/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">Figs 3b and 3c</figureCitation>
) orange-brown, sutures darker. Wings (
<figureCitation id="A8A6D4E2FFBFFF846E718199FCC308D1" box="[774,857,1418,1444]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[186,1404,185,1953]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[179,1408,181,1953]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male imago of Bessierus riobranco sp. n. a. forewing; b. body, dorsal view; c. body, lateral view; d. genitalia, ventral view; e. penes, ventral view; f. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4397236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4397236/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">Fig. 3a</figureCitation>
): membrane of fore wings hyaline, veins C, Sc and R1 tinged with yellowish, remainder of veins yellowish, lighter rearward. Legs broken off and missing. 
<emphasis id="02E91475FFBFFF84685F81BEFA0708B2" bold="true" box="[1320,1437,1453,1479]" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="A8A6D4E2FFBFFF846DE881C1FEDD0899" box="[159,327,1490,1516]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[186,1404,185,1953]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[179,1408,181,1953]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male imago of Bessierus riobranco sp. n. a. forewing; b. body, dorsal view; c. body, lateral view; d. genitalia, ventral view; e. penes, ventral view; f. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4397236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4397236/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">Figs 3b and 3c</figureCitation>
): terga yellowish-brown, terga I light brown, terga II–VIII shaded with light brown, terga with light V-shaped area medially and laterally on anterior margin. Sterna grayish-white. Genitalia (
<figureCitation id="A8A6D4E2FFBFFF84690C81E5FB5A0B64" box="[1147,1216,1526,1553]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[186,1404,185,1953]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[179,1408,181,1953]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male imago of Bessierus riobranco sp. n. a. forewing; b. body, dorsal view; c. body, lateral view; d. genitalia, ventral view; e. penes, ventral view; f. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4397236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4397236/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">Figs 3</figureCitation>
d–3f): styliger plate yellowish-brown, forceps yellowish-brown, lighter towards apex; inner margin of basal 1/3 of forceps segment I straight. Penis yellowish-orange, close to each other, almost touching; base of each penis lobe, on outer margin, expanded; telopenis slender. Caudal filaments broken and missing.
</paragraph>
